abstract: Con Errico is 58, and appears to be aging rapidly under the strain of being the man on the spot in horse racing's longest and most puzzling investigation. That strain intensified Monday when a Federal Appellate Court in Manhattan refused to overturn the former jockey's conviction for racketeering in connection with the fixing of thoroughbred races at Aqueduct and Saratoga in 1974 and 1975.
